cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual SLAM and local map building using appearance-based methods. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the integration of the proposed method into a state-of-the-art VO/VSLAM system, which is commonly used in robotics applications. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses Multi-index Hashing (MIH) and an online hash table selection algorithm to reduce query overhead and local map size, which are machine learning techniques. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses an appearance prior to determine the local map contents, which is a form of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible category as it is a sub-category of cs.CV and the paper deals with visual SLAM and local map building using appearance-based methods.
